TITLE: Implementing the Common Failure Trait in Scala
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a common Failure trait and service-specific error types that extend it. This pattern allows for consistent error handling throughout the application with proper status codes and user-facing messages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hyperledger-identus/docs/blob/main/documentation/adrs/decisions/2024-01-16-use-zio-failures-and-defects-effectively.md#2025-04-21_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
trait Failure {
  val statusCode: StatusCode
  val userFacingMessage: String
}

sealed trait ConnectionServiceError(
                                     val statusCode: StatusCode,
                                     val userFacingMessage: String
                                   ) extends Failure

object ConnectionServiceError {
  final case class InvitationAlreadyReceived(invitationId: String)
    extends ConnectionServiceError(
      StatusCode.BadRequest,
      s"The provided invitation has already been used: invitationId=$invitationId"
    )
}
```

