TITLE: Implementing Database Queries with Quill in Scala
DESCRIPTION: Example code demonstrating how to use Quill to query a PostgreSQL database. It defines a Person case class and creates a query to retrieve people with ID 1, showing Quill's approach which generates SQL at compile time.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hyperledger-identus/docs/blob/main/documentation/adrs/decisions/2023-01-18-quill-library-for-sql-statement-generation.md#2025-04-21_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: scala
CODE:
```
import io.getquill._

val ctx = new SqlMirrorContext(PostgresDialect, "ctx")

case class Person(id: Int, name: String)

val q = quote {
  query[Person].filter(p => p.id == 1)
}

val result: List[Person] = ctx.run(q)
```

